<p><b>Wilson Alwyn "Snowflake" Bentley</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-09"><a href="/wiki/February_9" title="February 9">February 9</a></span>, 1865 – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="12-23"><a href="/wiki/December_23" title="December 23">December 23</a></span>, 1931), born in <a href="/wiki/Jericho_(town),_Vermont" title="Jericho (town), Vermont">Jericho</a>, <a href="/wiki/Vermont" title="Vermont">Vermont</a>, is the first known <a href="/wiki/Photography" title="Photography">photographer</a> of <a href="/wiki/Snow" title="Snow">snowflakes</a>. He perfected a process of catching flakes on black <a href="/wiki/Velvet" title="Velvet">velvet</a> in such a way that their images could be captured before they either melted or <a href="/wiki/Sublimation_(chemistry)" title="Sublimation (chemistry)">sublimated</a>.</p>
